result.execSummary:
Aaron U Cadotte was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Aaron U Cadotte was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Aaron U Cadotte in court, in custody pro se.  Troy D Cross appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court stated Oklahoma has declined to come and get defendant. ADA Cross did not object to dismissal of the proceedings. Court dismissed proceedings.

Defendant, Aaron U Cadotte, appeared with attorney Randy Holtz of the public defender's office. Jane E. Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waived extradition. Court advised defendant of his rights. Court accepted waiver of right to challenge extradition. Defendant signed papers. Oklahoma to be picked up by Oklahoma officials within 10 days. If not, Court to be advised and hearing will be set.
